Defendant Roosevelt Rodney Means in court with attorney Donald Crawford Dudley.  Joshua M. Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy Court Clerk kmh.
Letters on behalf of the defendant received and filed. Statements made as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1 -   
Court ordered defendant to serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence; straight time/no good time; credit for 1 day time served.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered 60 days of condition time in the House of Correction - this is STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent.
2) Complete 100 hours of community service (adults only); 
3) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause; 
4) Continue to comply with psychiatric treatment from Gateway for Change, Fokus Family Services and take all prescribed medication; 
5) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
6) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
7) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
8) Fully comply with the sex offender registry;
9) Screen for sex offender treatment and comply with any ongoing treatment; 
10) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
11) Pay all supervision fees;
12) Pay applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments while on probation; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant. 
13) Attend the probation review hearing on 1/9/2015 at 8:30 a.m. in Br 44. 
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting and Child sex offender working with children.
Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
